    "K-value selectionThe selection of K value has a great influence on K-means, which is also the biggest disadvantage of K-means.",
    "Common methods for selecting K value include elbow method and Gap statistic method.If we get a sample, there are objectively J \"natural subclasses\", these real subclasses are hidden in the data.",
    "Below 3D data we can also draw a picture to distinguish the approximate number of J with the naked eye, higher dimensions can not be intuitively seen, we can only start from a relatively small K, such as K=2, to try to approximate the true value of J.1) When K is smaller than the real cluster number J of the sample, the degree of aggregation of each cluster will be greatly increased with each increase of one unit of K, and the distance sum will decrease greatly;2) When K approaches J, the return of polymerization degree obtained by increasing K will rapidly decrease, and the decline of distance sum will also decrease;3) As K continues to increase, the change of distance sum will be gradual.",
